Definite Article : Groups

We often use the when we talk about a well-know group as a whole (nothing that we don't 
use an article if we are talking about the members of that group)

Teachers work hard.
(each teacher works hard)

The teacher are going on strike. 
(the general group called "the teachers" is going to strike)

Poor people need our help.
(all poor people)

The poor in our city need help.
(the general group)

We also use the when we talk about nationalities as a group.

Canadians are not the same as Americans.

The Canadians are angry about the new rule.

